		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Subpixel rendering</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:182px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Subpixel_demonstration_(Quartz).png" class="image" title="Subpixel rendering works by increasing the luminance reconstruction points of a color subpixelated screen, such as a liquid crystal display (LCD). This thumbnail image is downsized and does not show the technique. Click to see the full-size image."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0d/Subpixel_demonstration_%28Quartz%29.png/180px-Subpixel_demonstration_%28Quartz%29.png" width="180" height="128" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Subpixel_demonstration_(Quartz).png" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
Subpixel rendering works by increasing the luminance reconstruction points of a color subpixelated screen, such as a liquid crystal display (LCD). This thumbnail image is downsized and does not show the technique. Click to see the full-size image.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><b>Subpixel rendering</b> is a way to increase the apparent resolution of a computer's <a href="/wiki/Liquid_crystal_display" title="Liquid crystal display">liquid crystal display</a> (LCD) by rendering pixels to take into account the screen type's physical properties. It takes advantage of the fact that each <a href="/wiki/Pixel" title="Pixel">pixel</a> on a color LCD is actually composed of individual red, green, and blue <a href="/wiki/Subpixel" title="Subpixel" class="mw-redirect">subpixel</a> stripes to <a href="/wiki/Anti-aliasing" title="Anti-aliasing">anti-alias</a> text with greater detail.</p>
<table id="toc" class="toc" summary="Contents">
